President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Iowa due to a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred in December 2009. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and emergency protective measures. Hazard mitigation measures will also be funded on a cost-sharing basis statewide. Thomas A. Hall has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.